==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Abaddon
<hw>A*bad"don</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*b⟦acr⟧d"d⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Heb. <ets>⟦amac⟧badd⟦omac⟧n</ets> destruction, abyss, fr.
<ets>⟦amac⟧bad</ets> to be lost, to perish.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
destroyer, or angel of the bottomless pit; -- the same as Apollyon and
Asmodeus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hell; the bottomless pit.</def>
<mark>[Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In all her gates, <qex>Abaddon</qex> rues⟦br⟧
Thy bold attempt.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Abaft</ent>⟦br⟧
